<h2 id="git-branch-display">Git branch displayÂ </h2>

<p>Eventually I got tired of having to do a â€˜git branchâ€™ when I wanted to check the current branch Iâ€™m working on, so I installed the git bash completion bash (src: <a href="https://github.com/bobthecow/git-flow-completion/wiki/Install-Bash-git-completion">https://github.com/bobthecow/git-flow-completion/wiki/Install-Bash-git-completion</a>). After that youâ€™ll need to add a function that gets the current branch name from the project youâ€™re currently standing on. Hereâ€™s what youâ€™ll need to add in the bash_profile in order to do that:</p>

